't. What the /corpse command does simply is, if you are within semi close distance of one of your corpses, it will summon it to where you are standing. I hope this helps some. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=calebe>Calebe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 602<br> <font color=#333333>(1/19/03 8:45:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Life as a mage</span><hr size=1> A friend used to play a bard back when the game was new. He was a human bard, born in Qeynos, and was the adventorous type.<br>
